PartialSyncHealthClient failed to update the health status to Scale Unit health blob

Our notifications are expected to be split among regions unevenly, based on the expected load size each region should support. 
Use "ARM Notifications Redistribution" dashboard linked in email to check that the same amount of notifications is still flowing, and just the distribution changed. If it is not the case, contact Notification V team.

[Deployment case] The notifications will be redistributed differently than we are expecting initially due to other regions temporary supporting traffic while deployed region regains processing capabilities, and it will take a while for the balance to be regained. This is a possible case when the monitor will be triggered, but no action should be taken except for monitoring no data is lost.

[Normal day case] Try to identify what could have been the reason (multiple nodes down, regional failures). If nothing seems to be the case, contact Notification Vteam.

monitors.description:
Keeps track of  the number of messages that failed to be queued to Event Hub from the NotificationsService. 
These will be retried by the Event Grid. But if we are failing a lot, EventGrids may identify our endpoint as degraded and messages will be delayed. 

If it is happening only in one region, consider moving traffic from this region.
